olive oil
1 Carrot
1 packet Green beans
1 packet Asian Greens
2 clove Garlic
1 packet Egg Noodles
2 packet Sesame Dressing
1 tbs soy sauce
2 eggs
1 packet pork mince
1 packet ginger paste
1 packet hoisin sauce
1 sachet Crispy Shallots

• Boil the kettle.
• Thinly slice carrot into half-moons. Trim green beans and cut into thirds. Roughly chop Asian greens. Finely chop garlic.
• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat.
• Cook carrot and green beans until tender, 4-6 minutes.
• Add Asian greens and garlic and cook until fragrant, 1 minute. Season and transfer to a bowl.

• While veggies are cooking, half-fill a medium saucepan with boiling water.
• Cook egg noodles over a medium-high heat, stirring occasionally with a fork to separate, until tender, 4-5 minutes.
• Drain, rinse with warm water, then return noodles to the saucepan.
• Add sesame dressing and the soy sauce. Toss to combine. Cover to keep warm.

• Return the frying pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. When oil is hot, crack the eggs into the pan. Cook until egg whites are firm and yolks are cooked to your liking, 4-5 minutes. Transfer to a plate.
• Return the frying pan to high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook pork mince, breaking up with a spoon, until just browned, 3-4 minutes.
• Add ginger paste and hoisin sauce and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Remove from heat. Add veggies and noodles. Toss to combine.

TIP: Add a splash of water if the noodles look dry!

• Divide sesame-hoisin pork noodles between bowls.
• Top with a fried egg and sprinkle over crispy shallots. Enjoy!